USER INTERVIEW SUMMARY (Revised for API Integration)

The primary user is a Queens College student who wants a simple and effective way to stay consistent with their fitness routine. The user expressed frustration with remembering previous workouts, planning new sessions, and tracking long-term progress. They prefer a clean, easy-to-use interface that allows quick workout logging and later viewing progress trends.

Interview Insights

Works out 3–4 times per week and wants a structured way to track improvements.

Logs exercise name, sets, reps, weight, and sometimes notes about performance.

Wants a progress dashboard showing:

weekly volume

PR progression

weight trends

Wants reminders when inactive for several days.

Wants goal-setting features (e.g., “bench 135,” “squat 225”).

Prefers simple UI with more detailed data when needed.

Would use the app daily if logging is fast and if charts update instantly.

Identified User Needs

A way to quickly log workouts

A visual dashboard to show improvements

Consistency reminders

Goal-setting tools

Ability to view coach feedback

Ability to track progress anytime, even from outside the web UI (API future support)

B. USER STAKEHOLDER REQUIREMENTS (SR1.x — Updated With API Integration)
### A. User Requirements — SR1.x (Updated With API Integration)

1. **SR1.1 – Log Workouts (UI + API)**
   Users shall be able to log workouts manually through a web form.
   This functionality shall also be accessible via a `POST` API endpoint for future mobile or external clients.

2. **SR1.2 – View Workout History (UI + API)**
   Users shall be able to view their complete workout history on a dashboard.
   The same data shall be retrievable via a secure JSON API endpoint.

3. **SR1.3 – View Progress & Trends (API-Backed Dashboard)**
   Users shall be able to view progress charts powered by backend API data (volume, consistency, PR trends).

4. **SR1.4 – Manage Account (UI + API)**
   Users shall be able to update their profile/password through the web UI.
   API endpoints shall allow the same updates for future clients.

5. **SR1.5 – Receive Coach Feedback (UI + API)**
   Users shall be able to view coach feedback on their dashboard.
   Feedback shall also be retrievable through a JSON API endpoint.

6. **SR1.6 – Secure Access to Personal Data (API Security)**
   Users shall have private access only to their own data via authenticated API calls.

C. WHAT CHANGED FROM THE PREVIOUS VERSION? (User Role)
### What Changed in the User Stakeholder Requirements

- **Added API support** to all major User functions (logging workouts, viewing history, etc.).
- **Workout logging** now explicitly includes a POST API endpoint.
- **Workout history** can now be accessed through JSON, not only through JSP pages.
- **Progress dashboard** is now described as API-powered instead of JSP-only.
- **Account management** now includes the ability to update user settings through API calls.
- **Coach feedback viewing** now includes API integration, enabling cross-platform access.
- **Security requirement added** so users can only access their own data via authenticated API requests.
